Malin Brdo, SLOVAKIA - Two mountain bikers in Slovakia's Malin Brdo Bike Park may or may not have expected to see a big brown bear while on their bike trail.Regardless, they reacted as if they were NOT expecting it.But the park lies in the Liptov region at the foothills of the Big Fatra, which is in the central to northern region of the country.The country's bears mostly live there too!* Watch the video in the gallery above. - YouTube.com/Du an Vin k